To analyze the sentence and calculate the average dependency distance, let's first break down the sentence into tokens and identify the head for each token:

1. Afrikas - head: odlingar (distance: 1)
2. odlingar - head: vara (distance: 4)
3. Det - head: vara (distance: 5)
4. kan - head: vara (distance: 4)
5. vara - head: livnära (distance: 4)
6. ganska - head: svårt (distance: 2)
7. svårt - head: livnära (distance: 6)
8. att - head: livnära (distance: 7)
9. livnära - head: eftersom (distance: 9)
10. sig - head: livnära (distance: 5)
11. på - head: livnära (distance: 6)
12. växter - head: livnära (distance: 5)
13. i - head: Afrika (distance: 1)
14. Afrika - head: livnära (distance: 8)
15. eftersom - head: livnära (distance: 9 - this is an adverbial clause, so we use a distance corresponding to its order and as dependent of the verb)
16. det - head: är (distance: 1)
17. är - head: livnära (distance: 6, corresponding to dependency i. the adverbial in this case; if included, head is torr and 5 in this specific particular case.)
18. så - head: torr (distance: 1)
19. torr - head: är (distance: 2)
20. mark - head: är (distance: 3)
21. . - this punctuation mark depends on livnära (distance: 11)

Average dependency distance is calculated as the sum of the distances divided by the number of tokens:

Sum of distances: 1 + 4 + 5 + 4 + 4 + 2 + 6 + 7 + 9 + 5 + 6 + 5 + 1 + 8 + 9 + 1 + 6 + 5 + 1 + 2 + 3 + 11
Sum of distances: 101

Number of tokens: 22

Average dependency distance: 101 / 22 ≈ 4.59